WEBVTT

00:16.558 --> 00:17.434
Hey.

00:18.643 --> 00:21.771
I know you're scared,
and I know you're angry,

00:21.855 --> 00:24.274
but I promise you,
we are here to help you.

00:24.357 --> 00:26.818
Hey, Derek, Derek.

00:26.901 --> 00:29.279
If you keep doing that,
you're gonna hurt yourself.

00:29.362 --> 00:32.782
Just calm down so we can talk, okay?

00:34.617 --> 00:36.119
Do you know who I am?

00:36.202 --> 00:37.829
An evil child kidnapper.

00:39.497 --> 00:41.875
Okay, I understand
why you would think that,

00:41.958 --> 00:44.002
but I'm not evil.

00:44.085 --> 00:47.505
I'm just a mom, a regular mom.

00:47.589 --> 00:49.758
That's my son, Will.

00:50.300 --> 00:51.384
Zombie boy.

00:51.468 --> 00:53.303
You know why they call him that?

00:53.386 --> 00:55.555
Because he died and came back to life.

00:55.638 --> 00:59.225
But what people don't know is
that when he went missing,

00:59.309 --> 01:03.229
he was taken by a terrible, scary monster.

01:03.313 --> 01:06.566
And now, that scary monster is after you.

01:06.649 --> 01:10.278
Yeah, I know. Mr. Whatsit told me,
which is why you need to let me go.

01:10.361 --> 01:13.823
No, no. Mr. Whatsit is not
who he says he is, okay?

01:13.907 --> 01:17.202
He is lying to you.
All these monsters, they work for him.

01:17.285 --> 01:20.705
That's why we took you here to this barn.
We thought this barn was safe,

01:20.789 --> 01:21.790
but he's found us.

01:21.873 --> 01:24.584
So we have to move you again,
somewhere he can't find you.

01:24.667 --> 01:28.630
So if I untie you,
will you cooperate and come with us?

01:30.006 --> 01:31.299
Please?

01:32.634 --> 01:33.468
Okay, great.

01:34.094 --> 01:37.597
You're a very brave kid, Derek.
I want you to know that.

01:37.680 --> 01:39.099
Very--

01:46.815 --> 01:49.567
-Let me go! Get off of me!
-Derek. Please!

01:49.651 --> 01:51.528
-The door! Get the door!
-Help me!

01:51.611 --> 01:53.279
Let me go! Get off me!

01:53.363 --> 01:55.949
-Stay down!
-Get away!

01:56.032 --> 01:58.827
Somebody help! I'm being kidnapped!

01:58.910 --> 02:01.037
Get away from me! Let me go!

02:01.621 --> 02:03.081
Mom, the rope! I need the rope!

02:04.124 --> 02:06.626
-Let me go! Eat dirt!
-Ah!

02:09.546 --> 02:11.172
Come try us, dipshit!

02:11.256 --> 02:12.215
Shit!

02:23.518 --> 02:25.687
Dude! She's not lying to you, okay?

02:25.770 --> 02:29.190
Mr. Whatsit is a very bad guy.
He sent the monsters after you.

02:29.274 --> 02:30.817
Suck my fat one!

02:30.900 --> 02:32.110
Jesus! What?

02:32.193 --> 02:34.445
You just signed
your death warrant, dipshit!

02:34.529 --> 02:36.406
You're a psycho, and you're going to jail!

02:36.489 --> 02:38.992
-There is a monster coming!
-We're trying to help you.

02:39.075 --> 02:40.827
-La, la, la, la.
-Derek, please!

02:40.910 --> 02:42.120
You gotta come down.

02:42.203 --> 02:44.205
I'm not listening. La, la, la, la.

03:07.604 --> 03:08.855
Stay back!

03:18.656 --> 03:21.367
You want him,
you're gonna have to come through me!

03:47.018 --> 03:49.229
Yeah, we got him! We got him!

04:07.538 --> 04:09.332
It flipped! It's headed back towards us!

04:09.415 --> 04:11.501
Come on. What are you doing, man?
We gotta turn around!

04:11.584 --> 04:13.544
Wait. Gates are like
Peanut Butter Boppers, right?

04:13.628 --> 04:16.506
-What?
-The outside is, like, crunchy and tough.

04:16.589 --> 04:19.133
But bite down on it,
it gives way to a gooey, creamy core.

04:19.217 --> 04:21.010
Dude, what the hell are you talking about?

04:21.094 --> 04:23.638
I drive fast enough,
the beamer can punch a hole into the gate,

04:23.721 --> 04:26.933
and then we can track the Demo
on its home turf in the Upside Down.

04:27.016 --> 04:29.060
-Follow it back home.
-We're losing the signal!

04:29.143 --> 04:31.062
We won't be able to follow anything
if we crash!

04:31.145 --> 04:32.772
We won't crash if it's like a Bopper!

04:32.855 --> 04:33.773
It's almost gone!

04:36.609 --> 04:37.610
Do it.

04:41.864 --> 04:43.825
-Oh my God! Oh my God!
-Jesus.

04:43.908 --> 04:45.827
-Oh my God! Oh my God!
-I got it! I got it!

04:46.494 --> 04:47.620
Oh God, no!

04:47.704 --> 04:49.539
-It's not gonna work.
-We're not gonna make it!

04:49.622 --> 04:52.583
-It's not a Bopper. Stop!
-Slow down! Jesus Christ!

04:52.667 --> 04:54.836
-Shit! Oh my God!
-Hang on!

05:02.719 --> 05:04.554
We did it! Woo!

05:07.015 --> 05:07.974
Signal?

05:09.267 --> 05:11.102
-Strong!
-Oh my God!

05:11.185 --> 05:13.896
We got you, son of a bitch! We got you!

05:30.330 --> 05:31.456
Will!? Will!

05:32.915 --> 05:35.168
I'm right here, Will.

05:35.251 --> 05:36.794
It's okay.

05:36.878 --> 05:38.963
I got you. I got you.

05:42.216 --> 05:43.801
I got you, sweetie.

06:47.365 --> 06:50.368
Uh, hockety-pockety?

06:50.451 --> 06:51.744
Oh, yes, yes, that's right.

06:51.828 --> 06:54.914
Hockety-pockety wockety wack
Odds and ends and bric-a-brac

06:54.997 --> 06:56.833
-I'll be with you in just a minute, son.
-What?

06:56.916 --> 06:58.334
Packing's almost done!

07:01.754 --> 07:02.922
Shush!

07:04.424 --> 07:05.425
Jelly!

07:12.056 --> 07:12.932
Alan Miller?

07:13.015 --> 07:15.226
I'm sorry, what is this about?

07:16.227 --> 07:17.854
It's your daughter, sir.

07:48.843 --> 07:51.179
Our boy's taking us on a shortcut
through Roane Cemetery.

07:51.262 --> 07:53.806
-That's almost at the county line.
-Doesn't this thing get tired?

07:53.890 --> 07:57.185
Unfortunately, it looks like the opposite.
I think he's speeding up.

07:57.268 --> 07:58.936
-What?
-I'm losing the signal.

07:59.020 --> 08:00.229
You've gotta be shitting me!

08:00.313 --> 08:01.814
-Can you go faster?
-Let's see.

08:05.318 --> 08:07.820
Henderson, you've gotta talk to me.
What do you got?

08:07.904 --> 08:10.031
-Henderson, what--
-I'm picking up interference.

08:10.114 --> 08:12.492
-How is that important?
-It means I can't hear the signal.

08:12.575 --> 08:14.160
-Listen harder.
-What do you mean?

08:14.243 --> 08:15.995
-You wanna put these on?
-I'm driving!

08:16.078 --> 08:17.955
You do the driving. I do the navigating.

08:18.039 --> 08:20.124
-What is that?
-I don't know.

08:20.208 --> 08:21.459
Steve, slow down.

08:21.542 --> 08:23.127
Is he ahead of us or not?

08:23.211 --> 08:25.713
-Steve!
-Steve, watch out!

08:25.796 --> 08:27.632
-Steve, watch out!
-Shit!

08:33.137 --> 08:36.557
Jonathan,
it's Mom. Answer me, please. Over.

08:37.058 --> 08:38.976
Jonathan, please answer.

08:39.644 --> 08:44.815
Jonathan, Nancy, Dustin, it's Joyce.
Please answer me.

08:45.608 --> 08:46.442
Hey.

08:46.526 --> 08:47.693
Any luck?

08:49.028 --> 08:52.698
Well, on the plus side,
I guess that means they made it through.

08:52.782 --> 08:54.325
Do you wanna see where they're headed?

09:25.022 --> 09:26.315
What is it?

09:26.399 --> 09:27.733
I don't know,

09:27.817 --> 09:32.738
but I could feel it's important to him.

09:33.239 --> 09:35.908
To Mr… Whatsit?

09:35.992 --> 09:37.535
His real name is Henry.

09:37.618 --> 09:38.578
AKA Vecna.

09:38.661 --> 09:39.745
AKA One.

09:39.829 --> 09:41.372
That's too many names.

09:41.455 --> 09:44.166
Why won't you just zip it
and listen, dipshit?

09:44.250 --> 09:47.128
I had this feeling
he didn't want me there.

09:48.838 --> 09:50.631
I wasn't supposed to see it.

09:51.632 --> 09:54.010
You've never been this close
to the hive mind before.

09:54.093 --> 09:56.887
I mean, that thing was, like, feet away.

09:58.681 --> 10:01.934
Sometimes at The Squawk,
when a signal comes in too strong,

10:02.018 --> 10:03.853
it overloads the whole system.

10:03.936 --> 10:06.480
I think that's what this was, an overload.

10:06.564 --> 10:08.983
You didn't just tap into the hive mind.

10:09.066 --> 10:12.403
You jacked right in
to the goddamn control center.

10:12.486 --> 10:14.697
And Holly. Where was Holly?

10:14.780 --> 10:17.658
Holly. Holly, she was…

10:17.742 --> 10:21.120
She was attached to this… this spire.

10:22.163 --> 10:26.667
And she became a part of it somehow,
like it was doing something to her.

10:28.419 --> 10:29.795
And… And there were others.

10:31.088 --> 10:32.590
There were three others.

10:35.384 --> 10:37.845
I thought
Vecna was just coming for dipshit.

10:37.928 --> 10:41.098
So did I. But I only knew about Derek
because he walked right past me.

10:43.684 --> 10:45.061
Serendipitous timing.

10:45.144 --> 10:47.938
-You hear that? Serendipitous.
-I don't know what that means.

10:48.022 --> 10:51.233
I'm really not loving
all of these extra spires.

10:51.317 --> 10:54.862
I mean, night one, Vecna kidnaps Holly.
Night two, he takes three more.

10:54.945 --> 10:57.406
He's escalating. And he's coming for more.

10:57.490 --> 11:00.743
Eight more, if this is accurate,
which brings him to a total of 12.

11:00.826 --> 11:03.996
What does he want with them? And why kids?

11:04.080 --> 11:05.164
-And why 12?
-I don't know.

11:05.247 --> 11:07.249
But we have to stop him
before he takes any more

11:07.333 --> 11:10.252
and buy Dustin and the others time
to find this place, to find Holly.

11:10.336 --> 11:14.048
If we can pinpoint his exact targets,
we could get them out of Hawkins.

11:14.131 --> 11:15.383
And out of Vecna's reach.

11:15.466 --> 11:16.759
Did you forget we're quarantined?

11:16.842 --> 11:19.011
-That's not all.
-There's another problem.

11:19.095 --> 11:21.722
On the way here,
we saw soldiers load Debbie Miller

11:21.806 --> 11:23.683
onto a bus with a bunch more kids.

11:23.766 --> 11:26.769
We followed them for two blocks more,
and they loaded more kids onto it.

11:26.852 --> 11:29.897
I don't think
they were taking them to school.

11:29.980 --> 11:32.024
Vecna's not the only one
that wants these kids.

11:38.614 --> 11:42.159
Eleven was at the Wheeler house
the same night Holly was taken.

11:42.243 --> 11:45.454
Twenty-four hours later,
we've got three more missing kids.

11:45.538 --> 11:49.583
There's 73 children in Hawkins
between the age of nine and ten.

11:49.667 --> 11:53.379
If the pattern holds,
our next target will be from this group.

11:53.462 --> 11:57.216
And you believe
Eleven has taken these kids?

11:57.299 --> 11:58.467
For what purpose?

11:58.551 --> 12:02.012
Killing them, protecting them.
The reason doesn't matter.

12:02.096 --> 12:03.764
These children? Where are they now?

12:03.848 --> 12:07.226
Arriving at the MAC-Z any moment,
which is where I want you.

12:07.309 --> 12:09.979
I should be looking for Lt. Akers.
I find Akers, I find--

12:10.062 --> 12:12.106
You'll find a dead man.

12:12.189 --> 12:14.942
Report to the MAC-Z, Colonel.
That's an order.

12:22.074 --> 12:23.242
Major General.

12:25.202 --> 12:28.247
With all due respect,
these kids are in danger.

12:28.330 --> 12:30.541
To use them as bait seems…

12:31.792 --> 12:34.420
Seems what, Sergeant?

12:36.297 --> 12:37.339
Reckless.

12:38.966 --> 12:43.471
It's only reckless
if you fail to protect them.

12:44.221 --> 12:47.516
Are you telling me
you can't protect them, Sergeant?

12:48.058 --> 12:49.059
No, ma'am.

12:51.562 --> 12:52.563
Good.

13:06.410 --> 13:07.995
I'm sorry for scaring you.

13:09.705 --> 13:13.417
I haven't seen anyone
in… a really long time, so…

13:14.919 --> 13:16.545
I guess I got excited.

13:18.339 --> 13:20.758
Good news is it doesn't look that deep.

13:20.841 --> 13:22.301
Not enough for stitches.

13:23.135 --> 13:25.221
I bet it stings though, huh?

13:27.473 --> 13:29.558
You can talk to me, you know.

13:30.768 --> 13:31.894
I won't bite.

13:34.772 --> 13:36.565
You do remember me, right?

13:37.775 --> 13:39.485
I've been to your house.

13:39.568 --> 13:40.778
Like, a lot.

13:43.531 --> 13:46.617
You're Max, Max Mayfield.

13:46.700 --> 13:49.036
You skateboard
and never take off your Walkman.

13:49.119 --> 13:51.205
-That's me.
-But--

13:51.288 --> 13:53.874
How am I in here
when I'm in a coma in Hawkins General?

13:55.376 --> 13:58.087
That's a very reasonable question.

14:00.047 --> 14:02.383
We should get going.
It's not safe here. Come on.

14:03.384 --> 14:05.052
Where are we going?

14:05.135 --> 14:05.970
My home.

14:06.053 --> 14:08.222
Well, I can't go far.
I came here to meet Henry.

14:08.305 --> 14:10.099
-Do you know Henry?
-You could say that.

14:10.182 --> 14:13.978
He left me this note. See? And he told me
to meet him right here at the X.

14:14.061 --> 14:15.729
I think he's in trouble with the monsters.

14:15.813 --> 14:18.524
Henry is a lot of things, but in trouble
with the monsters is not one of them.

14:18.607 --> 14:20.693
-But the note says--
-I know what the note says.

14:20.776 --> 14:22.903
How do you know he's not in trouble?
He said hurry!

14:22.987 --> 14:26.198
Holly, I know what the note says
because Henry didn't write it. I did.

14:27.491 --> 14:30.870
I don't… I don't understand.

14:32.162 --> 14:33.163
I'm sorry.

14:34.623 --> 14:38.669
I didn't want to lie. I… I just…
I had to make sure that you came here.

14:39.795 --> 14:41.297
You're one of them, aren't you?

14:42.006 --> 14:43.340
-One of what?
-The monsters.

14:43.424 --> 14:46.302
-Do I look like a monster?
-I don't know. Maybe you're in disguise.

14:46.385 --> 14:48.512
You're dressed weird,
and you're in a coma.

14:48.596 --> 14:49.763
Okay.

14:50.472 --> 14:53.767
Well, would a monster know
that your brother tried to get a mohawk

14:53.851 --> 14:55.477
until your sister stopped him,

14:55.561 --> 14:58.522
saving him from possibly
the greatest social humiliation

14:58.606 --> 15:00.983
that a freshman has ever experienced
at Hawkins High?

15:02.026 --> 15:03.861
What color was this mohawk?

15:04.445 --> 15:05.446
Hot orange.

15:05.529 --> 15:09.575
And personally, I think the use
of the word "hot" is a bit ironic, but…

15:09.658 --> 15:11.243
People say I'm too negative.

15:11.327 --> 15:12.745
I just think I'm honest.

15:35.851 --> 15:36.852
Come on.

15:45.945 --> 15:46.987
Welcome.

16:05.297 --> 16:06.173
Hey.

16:06.674 --> 16:08.175
It even comes with a view.

16:31.281 --> 16:32.491
Where are we?

16:33.367 --> 16:34.785
In a memory.

16:34.868 --> 16:39.623
Which exists inside a world
of 1,000 memories.

16:39.707 --> 16:41.250
I know it might look nice,

16:42.084 --> 16:43.293
but it's not.

16:43.919 --> 16:46.755
This place, this world…

16:48.132 --> 16:49.216
It's a prison.

16:55.639 --> 16:56.849
Henry's prison.

17:22.958 --> 17:24.835
It's okay, sweetie.

17:24.918 --> 17:28.464
These are the good guys.
They're going to keep everyone safe.

17:28.547 --> 17:32.384
Just try and think of this
as a field trip.

17:32.468 --> 17:35.137
Mm-hmm. A learning expedition.

17:47.524 --> 17:53.030
Cargo has arrived.
I repeat, cargo has arrived.

17:55.449 --> 17:58.619
They're taking them into a barracks
second from the library.

18:06.418 --> 18:07.669
Tunnels.

18:12.633 --> 18:17.596
Yeah. See? The north tunnel of the MAC-Z
runs right underneath the barracks.

18:17.679 --> 18:19.890
-Lucky break.
-Bound to happen one of these days.

18:19.973 --> 18:21.683
Gonna need more luck
if we want this plan to work.

18:21.767 --> 18:24.603
If we're right, the military is trying
to protect these kids.

18:24.686 --> 18:26.480
So this barracks
is gonna be heavily guarded.

18:26.563 --> 18:28.982
We have to dig up
into the barracks, unnoticed,

18:29.066 --> 18:31.276
grab the kids, get them to Murray,
smuggle them out of Hawkins.

18:31.360 --> 18:33.487
All before anyone notices they're gone.

18:33.570 --> 18:35.239
-Dick.
-What?

18:35.864 --> 18:37.366
What? Oh.

18:37.866 --> 18:40.994
Sorry. Did I say that out loud?
I thought I was talking in my head.

18:41.078 --> 18:43.288
But you guys know
Tom, Dick, and Harry, right?

18:45.165 --> 18:47.626
Seriously? None of you have seen
The Great Escape?

18:47.709 --> 18:51.296
Basically, it's about these POWs, right?

18:51.380 --> 18:54.299
And they're stuck
in a barracks just like this one.

18:54.383 --> 18:56.176
They need to escape,
so they dig these tunnels,

18:56.260 --> 18:58.679
and they call their tunnels
Tom, Dick, and Harry.

18:58.762 --> 19:00.597
They have to hide the tunnels
from the Nazis.

19:00.681 --> 19:03.934
So they put Tom in this dark corner,
and they put Harry under the stove,

19:04.017 --> 19:08.147
and they put Dick in the washroom.
And personally, for us, I like Dick.

19:11.275 --> 19:15.863
Oh, um… Sorry. The washroom.
I actually don't even… Never mind.

19:15.946 --> 19:17.739
Okay, say we go with Dick.

19:18.532 --> 19:20.117
How do we find the washroom?

19:20.200 --> 19:21.743
And how do we get the kids to it?

19:21.827 --> 19:24.246
How do we know
which kids are being targeted by Vecna?

19:24.329 --> 19:27.833
We use an inside man,
someone who could get into the barracks,

19:27.916 --> 19:31.086
measure the distance to the washroom,
find out which kids have seen Mr. Whatsit,

19:31.170 --> 19:32.754
and somehow avoid the military.

19:32.838 --> 19:36.008
Well, that's a lovely plan,
but isn't it a tad…

19:36.091 --> 19:37.217
Mission Impossible-y.

19:37.301 --> 19:40.596
Yeah. I mean, Mike,
who are you gonna get to do this?

19:40.679 --> 19:41.763
Bond? Magnum?

19:41.847 --> 19:43.807
No, no, we don't want a superspy.

19:43.891 --> 19:46.560
We want the opposite.
We want someone no one would suspect.

19:47.144 --> 19:49.605
Someone that could just walk in,
no questions asked.

19:49.688 --> 19:52.065
The one kid
the military failed to wrangle.

19:59.031 --> 20:00.073
What?

20:29.645 --> 20:34.441
Two grunts in the tower by the west gate.

20:34.524 --> 20:36.902
One more in the tower by the east gate.

20:36.985 --> 20:39.112
One, two, three, four on the ground.

20:39.988 --> 20:42.574
I hope to God you're right,
and Vecna is in there,

20:42.658 --> 20:44.826
because we might just die
trying to break in.

20:44.910 --> 20:45.953
I am right.

20:46.036 --> 20:49.039
You can't be right about everything.
Your theories aren't exactly lining up.

20:49.623 --> 20:51.708
-Why not?
-You heard kryptonite.

20:51.792 --> 20:53.669
If Vecna's in there,
he doesn't have his powers.

20:53.752 --> 20:54.878
If he doesn't have his powers,

20:54.962 --> 20:57.130
how could he have anything to do
with Holly's kidnapping?

20:57.214 --> 20:58.882
You can ask him before I kill him.

20:59.800 --> 21:01.343
How high is that fence?

21:02.344 --> 21:04.012
Hey, you're not jumping that.

21:04.096 --> 21:05.389
Why not?

21:05.472 --> 21:09.726
Because this is not training.
This is a real-world situation.

21:09.810 --> 21:12.104
And that roof is metal.

21:12.646 --> 21:15.482
You hit that on a jump,
you're gonna alert the whole damn base.

21:15.565 --> 21:17.025
Not if I time it with the thunder.

21:17.109 --> 21:18.694
Yeah.

21:18.777 --> 21:20.237
It's seven seconds.

21:23.991 --> 21:30.998
One, two, three, four, five, six…

21:34.584 --> 21:35.419
Seven.

21:35.502 --> 21:36.962
Okay. You got lucky.

21:38.797 --> 21:40.340
-Hopper, do you copy?
-Dustin!

21:40.424 --> 21:41.925
Over. This is Dustin.

21:42.009 --> 21:44.511
Hopper, do you copy? This is Dustin.

21:44.594 --> 21:47.055
Hey, hey, it's Hop. I copy.

21:47.139 --> 21:49.891
Holy shit! Okay. They're alive!

21:49.975 --> 21:51.059
El! Ask about El.

21:51.143 --> 21:52.352
El. Is El with you? Over.

21:52.436 --> 21:54.271
Yes. I'm here. Over.

21:54.354 --> 21:56.356
Okay. Yay. Terrific.

21:56.440 --> 21:59.109
I don't know if you're caught up
in something important, but--

21:59.192 --> 22:00.193
-Dustin. Come on.
-Meet us!

22:00.277 --> 22:02.654
Meet us at Roane Cemetery church, please.

22:02.738 --> 22:05.741
Roane Cemetery. How the hell
are you contacting us from there?

22:05.824 --> 22:08.785
Right. You don't know.
We're in the Upside Down.

22:08.869 --> 22:09.828
What?

22:09.911 --> 22:12.956
Long story short, we're here to track
a Demogorgon using our telemetry tracker,

22:13.040 --> 22:15.959
only to then hit a wall. Literally.
Now, Steve's beamer is stuck,

22:16.043 --> 22:18.128
so we need El to come and pry it loose
using her powers

22:18.211 --> 22:20.005
so we can resume the search
for said Demogorgon

22:20.088 --> 22:23.258
which will, in theory, lead us to Holly.
Does any of this make sense?

22:23.342 --> 22:26.762
Do you need additional details?
Questions? Concerns? Over.

22:26.845 --> 22:28.013
You hit a wall?

22:29.139 --> 22:30.766
What kind of wall, exactly?

22:31.850 --> 22:36.271
Uh… it's a bit… hard to describe.

22:37.439 --> 22:38.982
-Sort of…
-Huge?

22:40.400 --> 22:41.401
Disgusting.

22:41.485 --> 22:43.570
Smells like Henderson's armpit.

22:44.071 --> 22:46.615
We hit the same thing,
but not at the Roane Cemetery.

22:46.698 --> 22:49.451
We hit it a quarter mile southeast
of the old Hagen Bridge.

22:50.243 --> 22:52.162
That's the opposite side of town.

22:53.455 --> 22:54.498
Fascinating.

22:54.581 --> 22:56.792
We don't know what it is,
but we think Holly's behind it.

22:56.875 --> 22:59.586
Don't bother trying to break through.
You can't.

23:00.128 --> 23:01.296
We're working on a solution.

23:02.297 --> 23:04.925
-Nancy.
-Solution? What kind of solution?

23:06.134 --> 23:08.678
Wait, what kind of solution? Hopper!

23:08.762 --> 23:11.473
Listen, we gotta keep the airwaves clear,
all right?

23:11.556 --> 23:13.850
We'll come get you. Just stay put.

23:15.769 --> 23:17.145
You think they're safe?

23:17.229 --> 23:18.939
I mean, compared to us? Yeah.

23:19.940 --> 23:20.941
Okay.

23:22.067 --> 23:24.027
Let's go see
if that training has paid off.

23:24.111 --> 23:25.904
You're gonna let me jump?

23:27.114 --> 23:29.324
Let's go before I change my mind.

23:36.790 --> 23:38.041
Vecna's curse,

23:39.459 --> 23:40.752
it never goes away.

23:41.628 --> 23:42.629
Never leaves you.

23:43.338 --> 23:46.383
With each victim that he took,
he created a new gate.

23:46.466 --> 23:48.510
A gate to the Upside Down?

23:49.511 --> 23:53.557
When he took me,
he opened the fourth, final gate,

23:53.640 --> 23:54.808
splitting Hawkins in two.

23:56.893 --> 24:03.608
Wait, but if Mr. Whatsit…
I mean Henry, took you, how are you here?

24:03.692 --> 24:05.193
You mean, shouldn't I be dead?

24:06.695 --> 24:08.864
It's okay. It's a fair question.

24:09.739 --> 24:10.866
I definitely should be.

24:11.825 --> 24:13.535
And for a moment…

24:14.995 --> 24:15.912
I was.

24:19.374 --> 24:21.084
I don't know how long I was gone.

24:21.168 --> 24:25.589
But then I felt something… calling to me.

25:17.057 --> 25:19.309
Life could be dream

25:19.392 --> 25:22.270
If I could take you up
In Paradise up above

25:23.021 --> 25:24.689
If you would tell me I'm the only…

25:24.773 --> 25:28.193
One night only. Don't miss it.
Tickets are only 50 cents.

25:28.276 --> 25:30.487
That's two quarters for you poindexters.

25:30.570 --> 25:35.158
-Joyce! This that stupid play of yours?
-I better see you there, Harrington.

25:35.242 --> 25:37.410
Friday night? You wish.

25:39.287 --> 25:40.330
Life could be dream

25:40.413 --> 25:41.915
Nice shot, jerk.

25:41.998 --> 25:44.042
If only all my precious plans
Would come true

25:45.335 --> 25:48.713
Somehow, I was in another time.

25:48.797 --> 25:50.131
Hawkins.

25:51.508 --> 25:52.968
Thirty years ago.

25:53.051 --> 25:54.177
Time travel.

25:55.095 --> 25:57.931
Only, I wasn't actually there.

25:58.557 --> 26:00.350
Not really. I was just…

26:01.643 --> 26:02.686
an observer.

26:06.106 --> 26:08.024
And that's when I understood.

26:08.733 --> 26:12.028
I was trapped inside Henry's mind,
his memories.

26:12.112 --> 26:15.073
Like a nightmare prison world

26:15.156 --> 26:19.119
ruled by an evil,
psychopathic piece of shit.

26:20.036 --> 26:21.162
Like Camazotz.

26:21.246 --> 26:23.206
Cama… What?

26:23.290 --> 26:25.542
Camazotz. From A Wrinkle in Time.

26:26.126 --> 26:27.544
-Never read it.
-You should. It's amazing.

26:27.627 --> 26:30.589
Camazotz is like this dark planet
that's under the control of IT,

26:30.672 --> 26:32.841
which is this giant,
disembodied, evil brain.

26:32.924 --> 26:34.926
Anyways, Meg's dad…
Meg's the main character.

26:35.010 --> 26:36.469
…he gets taken prisoner there.

26:36.553 --> 26:39.723
So, Henry's kinda like IT,
and you're kinda like Meg's dad.

26:39.806 --> 26:40.974
Okay. Well…

26:41.474 --> 26:44.853
I don't know if Meg's dad would agree,
but the way I see it,

26:44.936 --> 26:48.732
when you're a prisoner
in a messed up prison world,

26:48.815 --> 26:50.859
you really only have
a few doors open to you.

26:51.943 --> 26:54.738
Door one, you take your own life.

26:56.031 --> 26:58.700
Door two, accept your fate.

26:58.783 --> 27:01.161
-Or door three…
-You escape.

27:01.745 --> 27:04.414
-I chose door three.
-That seems like the best door.

27:05.415 --> 27:07.584
So, I kept moving.

27:08.168 --> 27:10.629
From memory to memory.

27:10.712 --> 27:13.840
Only, this place is a maze.

27:14.549 --> 27:19.012
I became lost, turned around.
I got so turned around,

27:19.095 --> 27:21.931
I actually ended up
right back at the beginning.

27:32.150 --> 27:33.735
And that's when I heard her.

27:37.072 --> 27:38.573
I heard Kate Bush.

27:39.157 --> 27:40.533
Is she one of your friends?

27:42.410 --> 27:43.453
You could say that.

27:43.536 --> 27:46.665
Do you wanna hear
About the deal that I'm making?

27:47.832 --> 27:51.586
Music has a way of finding you,
even in the darkest of places.

27:51.670 --> 27:55.882
Lucas had used it before, to reach me,
to guide me out of Vecna's mind,

27:56.466 --> 27:57.425
back to the light.

27:58.802 --> 28:02.806
If I only could make a deal with God

28:02.889 --> 28:05.975
And I'd get him to swap our places

28:06.059 --> 28:08.061
Be runnin' up that road

28:08.144 --> 28:13.316
So, this music was coming from Lucas,
from the real world?

28:18.405 --> 28:19.948
Even after all this time,

28:21.366 --> 28:22.826
he hadn't given up on me.

28:23.410 --> 28:25.662
If you follow this music,

28:26.621 --> 28:27.580
then what?

28:28.623 --> 28:30.625
Then it would lead me out of here.

28:32.585 --> 28:33.586
Back home.

28:35.880 --> 28:37.757
At least, that's what I thought.

28:40.510 --> 28:41.553
But then…

28:45.432 --> 28:47.308
everything went wrong.

28:47.392 --> 28:50.520
Oh, come on, angel
Come on, come on, darlin'

28:51.271 --> 28:53.064
Let's exchange the…

29:13.501 --> 29:14.794
Hey!

29:15.879 --> 29:20.842
What the hell are you doing?
Can't you read, kid? No trespassing.

29:20.925 --> 29:22.844
Right, I see that, officer.

29:22.927 --> 29:25.513
It's just… my school is missing.

29:31.603 --> 29:33.229
Let's go.

29:43.490 --> 29:44.574
Move it.

29:49.996 --> 29:52.707
Holy shit! Are those laser blasters?

29:52.791 --> 29:54.083
Might just be.

29:54.167 --> 29:56.628
And they'll blast you
if you don't keep it moving.

30:00.924 --> 30:02.884
-Boys.
-Can't get me!

30:02.967 --> 30:03.968
Boys!

30:05.929 --> 30:08.348
All right. Absolutely not.

30:09.140 --> 30:10.850
Whoa. Whoa. Whoa. Whoa.

30:11.518 --> 30:14.521
This is Private Chapman.
You do exactly as he says.

30:14.604 --> 30:17.273
You got any questions, direct them to him.

30:17.357 --> 30:20.235
Where might I relieve myself?

30:22.904 --> 30:24.197
Breaking bar.

30:24.989 --> 30:26.115
Shovel.

30:27.492 --> 30:29.369
Five safety goggles.

30:30.370 --> 30:32.622
A surveyor's wheel and…

30:32.705 --> 30:34.165
Hold for applause.

30:37.961 --> 30:41.214
Santa's sleigh is ready for his reindeer.

30:41.297 --> 30:45.635
We got built-in benches,
seat belts, foam padding.

30:45.718 --> 30:48.429
Everything a kidnapped child could desire.

30:48.513 --> 30:49.597
Foam padding?

30:49.681 --> 30:52.934
Don't want to break any eggs en route,
now do we?

30:53.768 --> 30:57.647
I'm in. Do you copy?
Repeat, I'm in. Do you copy?

30:57.730 --> 31:00.316
Yes, yes, we copy. We copy. Where are you?

31:00.400 --> 31:03.820
Bathroom. Back stall.
45 of my paces from the front entrance.

31:03.903 --> 31:06.739
Good job. Now round up anyone
who's seen Mr. Whatsit,

31:06.823 --> 31:08.157
and we'll be there soon.

31:08.241 --> 31:11.661
And remember, you're not Dipshit Derek.
You're--

31:11.744 --> 31:13.079
Delightful Derek.

31:24.382 --> 31:28.928
Okay, once you get
that gate open, and I'm inside…

31:29.012 --> 31:30.972
-You lead.
-That's right.

31:31.055 --> 31:32.056
And you?

31:32.724 --> 31:36.436
I will destroy your kryptonite.
Don't worry.

31:37.604 --> 31:38.605
Okay.

32:20.563 --> 32:23.816
All right, come on.
Come on, you got this. You got this.

32:54.806 --> 32:56.474
Wait. You're too early. You're too early.

33:02.772 --> 33:03.690
God.

33:07.026 --> 33:07.944
Sorry.

33:12.782 --> 33:15.368
You trying to give
your old man a heart attack?

33:15.451 --> 33:16.953
Nice job, by the way.

33:23.960 --> 33:24.836
Hop?

33:24.919 --> 33:25.962
Yeah?

33:27.588 --> 33:28.589
Thank you.

33:29.215 --> 33:30.049
For what?

33:30.633 --> 33:31.759
For teaching me.

33:33.511 --> 33:34.887
And trusting me.

33:36.347 --> 33:37.348
Always.

33:44.063 --> 33:46.441
The day of reckoning has arrived.

33:46.524 --> 33:48.818
With this in mind,
I've been sent by Mr. Whatsit

33:48.901 --> 33:50.153
to gather the chosen ones.

33:50.236 --> 33:52.822
If you've been visited by Mr. Whatsit,
speak now.

33:52.905 --> 33:55.408
And when night falls,
follow me to the latrine,

33:55.491 --> 33:58.703
and I will lead you
to our savior, to safety.

34:00.079 --> 34:01.706
Derek's gone mental.

34:03.499 --> 34:06.294
The monsters are coming,
and you're all gonna die.

34:08.212 --> 34:09.255
Derek?

34:10.631 --> 34:12.175
Were you talking about Henry?

34:23.686 --> 34:25.354
Any word from Derek yet?

34:25.438 --> 34:26.773
Not yet.

34:26.856 --> 34:29.400
Just give him time.
It hasn't been that long.

34:29.484 --> 34:31.736
I just can't get over the fact

34:31.819 --> 34:36.282
that the fate of the world rests
on Derek freakin' Turnbow.

34:36.365 --> 34:39.535
When you look in the mirror, do you see
a Navy SEAL looking back at you?

34:39.619 --> 34:42.622
Sometimes people need
someone to believe in them.

34:43.915 --> 34:46.209
And then they can do amazing things.

34:46.709 --> 34:49.087
Your mom and Robin
are getting along better.

34:49.837 --> 34:52.924
Well, it didn't hurt
that Mom scared off that Demo.

34:53.007 --> 34:55.885
Saved Robin's life, everybody's life.

34:59.013 --> 35:02.642
So, when your mom, when she had her axe,

35:02.725 --> 35:04.018
you could see her?

35:04.102 --> 35:06.020
-Like, through the Demo's eyes?
-Yeah.

35:06.104 --> 35:08.481
And I was so close to the hive,

35:08.564 --> 35:13.111
it's like I could feel
what it was feeling, like this anger.

35:13.194 --> 35:15.571
That I was still in there too.

35:15.655 --> 35:17.949
And I was afraid. I was afraid for my mom.

35:18.032 --> 35:21.661
-You wanted to protect her.
-Yeah. But I… I just couldn't.

35:22.245 --> 35:25.039
It was like this scary movie
you just can't turn off.

35:28.000 --> 35:30.795
Open sesame.

35:32.046 --> 35:35.258
Oh. Well, have fun.

35:36.008 --> 35:37.051
Thanks.

35:37.927 --> 35:40.388
-Are you positive you didn't?
-Didn't what?

35:40.471 --> 35:41.556
Turn off the scary movie.

35:41.639 --> 35:43.307
Protect your mom,
not the other way around.

35:43.391 --> 35:46.060
No offense. I know she's badass
and everything, but you know.

35:46.144 --> 35:47.687
-Yeah, she's 5'3".
-Yeah!

35:47.770 --> 35:50.940
And Vecna likes to control the hive mind
like a puppet master.

35:51.023 --> 35:53.985
So maybe when you tap into the hive,
you can pull the strings too.

35:54.068 --> 35:56.154
Except I'm not Vecna.

35:56.237 --> 35:57.238
You sorta are.

35:57.947 --> 36:01.033
You're trying to say that I'm evil
and hell-bent on destroying the world?

36:01.117 --> 36:02.076
Totally.

36:02.160 --> 36:05.580
No, I'm just saying that, you know,
you're like a wizard like him.

36:05.663 --> 36:07.623
In D&D, Mike, not real life.

36:07.707 --> 36:10.084
True. In real life,
you're more like a sorcerer,

36:10.168 --> 36:13.004
because your powers don't come
from a book of spells. They're innate.

36:14.005 --> 36:17.175
Listen, as far as crazy theories go,
I've had crazier.

36:17.258 --> 36:20.428
And with Eleven in the Upside Down,
we really need some magic up here.

36:58.799 --> 37:00.551
Working on a solution?

37:00.635 --> 37:04.722
I mean, if Hopper has a solution
to get through this and to get to Holly,

37:04.805 --> 37:06.432
he should… he should share it with us!

37:06.515 --> 37:08.142
I just say we ignore the old man.

37:08.226 --> 37:10.853
We keep moving.
Look for a door or something.

37:10.937 --> 37:13.481
Yeah, and just curious.

37:13.564 --> 37:16.359
This door of yours,
it's soft like a Peanut Butter Bopper?

37:16.442 --> 37:18.527
You got something to say, Byers,
why don't you say it?

37:18.611 --> 37:21.239
I'm just saying maybe you shouldn't be
making the calls from now on.

37:21.322 --> 37:24.992
It was not just his call.
It was mine because it's my sister.

37:25.952 --> 37:26.953
And…

37:27.453 --> 37:30.373
I agree with Steve.
Okay, we can't just sit here.

37:30.456 --> 37:34.377
I don't know about a door,
but this wall can't go on forever.

37:34.460 --> 37:36.254
There has to be a way around it.

37:36.337 --> 37:37.380
There isn't.

37:38.172 --> 37:40.508
This wall is a circle.

37:40.591 --> 37:43.177
A circle completely surrounding
the Upside Down.

37:43.261 --> 37:44.679
Oh yeah? How do you figure that?

37:44.762 --> 37:47.431
Because unlike you,
I didn't sleep through Algebra 1.

37:50.268 --> 37:53.854
My telemetry tracker picked up
a weird frequency coming from the wall,

37:53.938 --> 37:57.233
and it took me a bit to place,
but I've heard it before.

37:57.316 --> 37:59.860
Rather, we have.
Remember when we were out looking for Hop,

37:59.944 --> 38:01.612
and you heard that sound
off of Irwin Road?

38:01.696 --> 38:04.156
-Yeah. You said it was interference.
-It was.

38:04.240 --> 38:07.952
But this interference, it wasn't coming
from a military broadcast or an EMI.

38:08.035 --> 38:10.788
It was coming from this wall,
which is important,

38:10.871 --> 38:13.374
because that gives us
three known locations.

38:13.457 --> 38:14.959
So, I connected the dots,

38:15.042 --> 38:17.670
measured the midpoints,
drew the perpendicular bisectors--

38:17.753 --> 38:21.090
All right! Yeah, we're not your teachers.
We don't need to see your work.

38:21.173 --> 38:23.259
We get it.
You think it's all a big circle.

38:23.342 --> 38:26.637
I don't think. I know. I triple checked,
and my calculations are correct.

38:26.721 --> 38:29.849
Whatever! I still don't see
how this gets us closer to finding Holly.

38:29.932 --> 38:33.144
Because it's not about the circle.
It's about the center.

38:35.354 --> 38:37.773
The DOE. The Department of Energy.

38:38.274 --> 38:40.359
-That's--
-Hawkins Lab.

38:41.152 --> 38:43.195
What are the chances
that the center of this wall

38:43.279 --> 38:45.656
happens to be in the place
where all of this started,

38:45.740 --> 38:47.658
where the Upside Down was created?

38:47.742 --> 38:49.327
So, the lab created the wall?

38:49.910 --> 38:52.663
No idea. But I think we should find out.

38:53.331 --> 38:54.248
Don't you?

39:01.464 --> 39:03.716
The music, it led me to a new memory.

39:04.300 --> 39:07.011
Only, something was different
about this memory.

39:07.511 --> 39:09.597
I was there.

39:10.973 --> 39:12.767
It was the day that Henry cursed me.

39:13.684 --> 39:15.227
It was his first memory of me.

39:16.645 --> 39:19.940
I know, as if this goddamn place
wasn't heady enough, right?

39:20.733 --> 39:23.319
But I still had the music to guide me.

39:23.903 --> 39:25.696
So I followed it.

39:27.198 --> 39:30.826
And it led me through new memories.

39:37.208 --> 39:38.709
Terrible memories.

39:38.793 --> 39:42.088
-Let go!
-Follow me into death.

39:56.811 --> 39:59.105
And it felt like they would never end.

40:02.441 --> 40:05.778
But then eventually, they did.

40:07.071 --> 40:10.032
It was the night that Vecna killed me.

40:12.827 --> 40:14.453
The night he took me prisoner.

40:15.704 --> 40:17.456
Yeah, yeah, yo

40:17.540 --> 40:20.167
Do you wanna know
Know that it doesn't hurt me?

40:20.251 --> 40:21.836
I'd finally found it.

40:21.919 --> 40:25.714
Do you wanna hear
About the deal that I'm making?

40:27.007 --> 40:28.551
The way out.

40:30.594 --> 40:34.348
It's you and me

40:34.849 --> 40:38.727
And if I only could
I'd make a deal with God

40:38.811 --> 40:40.813
And I'd get him to swap…

40:47.736 --> 40:49.321
And I was so close.

40:52.867 --> 40:55.619
So close
that I could feel his hand on mine.

40:58.456 --> 41:00.207
And it was like I was there.

41:01.500 --> 41:04.086
Like I was with him in that hospital.

41:12.845 --> 41:16.640
Come on, Angel
Come on, come on, darling

41:16.724 --> 41:20.394
Let's exchange the experience

41:31.530 --> 41:32.490
No.

41:33.491 --> 41:34.366
No.

41:39.830 --> 41:40.831
Lucas!

41:41.999 --> 41:45.878
Lucas! Lucas! Lucas!

41:49.381 --> 41:50.508
Hello, Max.

41:54.178 --> 41:55.763
I ran.

41:58.641 --> 41:59.850
And I kept running.

42:33.050 --> 42:35.553
I'll never forget
the look on his face that day.

42:36.512 --> 42:38.472
He was scared.

42:38.556 --> 42:42.184
More than scared, he was terrified.

42:42.768 --> 42:44.603
There's something about this cave…

42:46.063 --> 42:47.064
this memory.

42:49.775 --> 42:50.901
He won't come in.

42:52.695 --> 42:53.696
In here,

42:54.822 --> 42:55.823
I'm safe.

42:56.740 --> 42:59.868
So I turned it into my sanctuary.

43:03.539 --> 43:04.540
My home.

43:07.418 --> 43:08.627
I took door two.

43:10.504 --> 43:11.755
Shitty door two.

43:14.174 --> 43:15.593
Accept your fate.

43:16.635 --> 43:17.678
That was,

43:18.804 --> 43:20.222
until you showed up.

43:21.473 --> 43:23.267
And now door three is back.

43:24.727 --> 43:25.853
Escape.

43:26.520 --> 43:29.231
I have a plan,
a plan to get us out of here.

43:29.940 --> 43:33.277
And it's gonna take time,
more time than we have now.

43:33.360 --> 43:35.487
Henry will return to his house soon.

43:35.571 --> 43:38.407
And when he does,
he cannot know that you're gone.

43:38.490 --> 43:40.284
You want me to go back there?

43:41.243 --> 43:42.828
Back to him? Back to Henry? No, I--

43:42.911 --> 43:44.872
I know. It's scary.

43:44.955 --> 43:50.085
But if you wanna get out of here,
if you wanna escape Camazotz,

43:50.669 --> 43:52.087
this is the only way.

43:53.797 --> 43:55.049
It's the only way.

44:00.554 --> 44:02.097
Tell me what I need to do.

44:21.033 --> 44:21.909
Hey, wh--

44:21.992 --> 44:23.243
-Hey.
-Hi.

44:26.747 --> 44:30.042
Do you, um, by any chance,
remember Tammy Thompson?

44:30.125 --> 44:32.836
Yeah. Isn't she that terrible singer?

44:32.920 --> 44:34.588
Yeah.

44:34.672 --> 44:36.090
But in the ninth grade,

44:36.173 --> 44:39.802
I thought that she sounded
like Whitney goddamn Houston.

44:39.885 --> 44:45.391
I mean, the first time I saw her,
oh my God, like, time slowed down.

44:45.474 --> 44:47.976
It was like a scene
from some lame-o movie.

44:48.060 --> 44:52.064
You know, her hair blew in the wind,
and she just looked perfect.

44:52.940 --> 44:54.274
So goddamn perfect.

44:54.358 --> 44:57.861
And, uh, it was right then and there
that I knew she was the one.

44:58.445 --> 45:02.908
That with Tammy, I would finally be able
to be myself, you know, all of myself.

45:04.118 --> 45:08.414
Because there was always this part of me
that kind of scared me, you know?

45:08.497 --> 45:12.418
But I thought
that if Tammy loved me, all of me,

45:12.501 --> 45:15.879
you know, I wouldn't be so scared anymore.

45:15.963 --> 45:19.383
And then he showed up,
Steve "The Hair" Harrington.

45:19.466 --> 45:20.926
Oh God.

45:21.009 --> 45:22.678
You probably can guess the rest.

45:22.761 --> 45:25.472
Tammy fell for him hard.

45:26.056 --> 45:31.437
And my entire fantasy life with her,
along with the rest of my life,

45:31.520 --> 45:33.272
pretty much imploded before my eyes.

45:33.355 --> 45:35.524
I mean, my grades plummeted.
I got grounded.

45:35.607 --> 45:37.693
I had to stay home every weekend
doing chores.

45:37.776 --> 45:41.029
But then one day, I was cleaning bat shit
out of my parents' garage,

45:41.113 --> 45:43.574
and I found this 8-millimeter film reel.
You know?

45:43.657 --> 45:46.952
And it was just from this silly movie
that I made in fourth grade,

45:47.035 --> 45:48.871
but I got it up on the projector,

45:48.954 --> 45:53.792
and all of a sudden, I was looking
at this little version of myself.

45:53.876 --> 45:57.254
And that little me,
I could hardly recognize her.

45:57.337 --> 46:00.591
You know, she was so carefree

46:01.717 --> 46:04.011
and, like, fearless.

46:04.678 --> 46:06.555
She just loved every part of herself.

46:07.890 --> 46:09.141
And that's when it hit me.

46:09.808 --> 46:12.352
It was never about Tone-deaf Tammy.

46:13.604 --> 46:16.815
It was always just about me.

46:17.524 --> 46:19.818
I was looking for answers
in somebody else, but…

46:21.820 --> 46:23.822
I had all the answers.

46:24.698 --> 46:27.534
I just needed to stop being
so goddamn scared.

46:28.535 --> 46:31.914
Scared of… who I really was.

46:32.915 --> 46:34.958
Once I did that, oh,

46:36.043 --> 46:37.795
I felt so free.

46:38.587 --> 46:42.090
It's like I could fly, you know?
Like, I could finally be…

46:42.174 --> 46:43.550
Rockin' Robin.

46:44.843 --> 46:47.137
Yeah. Rockin' Robin.

46:48.347 --> 46:49.890
Hey, guys!

46:49.973 --> 46:51.433
Take your time, will ya?

46:56.647 --> 46:58.023
Did you finally hit Dick?

46:58.106 --> 46:59.608
-Hit the Dick.
-Yep.

46:59.691 --> 47:01.693
Let's just hope it's not too hard.

47:01.777 --> 47:02.861
If it is,

47:03.862 --> 47:04.947
I'll soften it.

47:10.661 --> 47:11.537
Hey!

47:12.788 --> 47:13.831
Hey!

47:15.207 --> 47:16.458
Hey!

47:18.585 --> 47:19.920
Take me to Kay.

47:40.732 --> 47:41.859
Damn it! Damn it!

47:46.405 --> 47:49.658
Make a sound, it'll be your last.
Nod if you understand.

47:52.536 --> 47:55.247
Move! Move it! Come on, let's go!

47:56.081 --> 47:57.082
Come on!

47:59.167 --> 48:00.252
It's not working.

48:01.461 --> 48:03.338
-How do we get through?
-I don't have clearance.

48:03.422 --> 48:06.592
I didn't ask if you have clearance.
I asked, how do we get through?

48:06.675 --> 48:07.801
You can't.

48:07.885 --> 48:11.388
Dr. Kay, your boss, she got clearance?

48:11.471 --> 48:12.514
I don't know.

48:13.348 --> 48:14.349
You don't know.

48:14.850 --> 48:16.935
Thanks for your help.

48:17.603 --> 48:18.604
Plan B.

48:42.628 --> 48:45.130
-Stop! Stop!
-El!

48:46.506 --> 48:48.133
-El!
-Stop!

49:26.254 --> 49:27.547
We're through.

49:36.431 --> 49:37.599
Oh, shit.

49:58.412 --> 49:59.371
Oh, shit.

50:05.544 --> 50:09.589
I want you to close your eyes
and focus on your breathing.

50:09.673 --> 50:11.925
Breathe in and out.

50:12.009 --> 50:14.011
As you continue breathing,

50:14.094 --> 50:16.888
I want you to picture yourself on a beach.

50:16.972 --> 50:20.434
The water is blue. Blue as a Smurf.

50:20.517 --> 50:26.064
You listen to it lap the sandy shore,
like a dog slurping from his bowl.

50:32.404 --> 50:35.198
It's called visualization.

50:35.282 --> 50:37.200
Mom does it when she's out of Valium.

50:49.629 --> 50:50.797
Go.

51:36.259 --> 51:37.177
Howdy.

51:41.598 --> 51:47.646
Feel the sand under your butt.
It feels cool and soft.

51:47.729 --> 51:49.898
…time. There you go.

51:50.941 --> 51:52.901
Good job, good job. All right.

51:53.902 --> 51:56.696
Hey, sweetie. Um, what's your name?

51:56.780 --> 51:58.198
Debbie.

51:58.281 --> 52:00.033
Do you work for Mr. Whatsit?

52:00.117 --> 52:01.243
Mr. Whatsit.

52:01.326 --> 52:04.704
Oh. Um, yes. Of course.
I'm one of his elves.

52:04.788 --> 52:07.582
You know, like a… a magic elf.

52:24.599 --> 52:27.394
Right here. A couple more steps.

52:27.477 --> 52:29.563
All right. Yes, okay.

52:29.646 --> 52:32.774
All right. Great job. Step by step.

52:48.582 --> 52:49.958
Shit.

53:27.078 --> 53:27.913
Eleven.

53:29.289 --> 53:33.293
I have been looking for you
for a very long time.

53:35.295 --> 53:36.171
My name is--

53:36.254 --> 53:37.339
Dr. Kay.

53:39.549 --> 53:41.259
I know who you are.

53:43.303 --> 53:45.347
I know who you've taken.

53:49.643 --> 53:51.102
And I also know…

53:53.647 --> 53:55.232
that you and your men…

53:57.067 --> 53:59.110
are going to die.

54:29.307 --> 54:30.600
What the hell?

55:35.582 --> 55:37.667
It's best not to struggle.

55:38.877 --> 55:43.340
The greater the perceived threat,
the more aggressive its response.

55:49.262 --> 55:51.139
Miss Robin, what about the others?

55:51.222 --> 55:53.600
Uh, just Robin. And don't worry.
They're right behind us.

55:53.683 --> 55:55.935
-Something's wrong, isn't it?
-No. No, siree.

55:56.019 --> 55:57.896
Everything is going
exactly according to plan.

55:58.938 --> 56:01.691
-Airlock-- Wrap it with your jacket.
-I got it.

56:01.775 --> 56:03.735
Hold it. Hold it. Hold it.

56:03.818 --> 56:05.362
Here. Try it--

56:07.530 --> 56:10.283
Hey. Sorry.
Bit of a plumbing problem here.

56:10.367 --> 56:12.243
Are you by chance looking for Mr. Whatsit?

56:13.536 --> 56:15.330
-Right through there.
-Right there.

56:25.340 --> 56:28.343
There's a little breeze
in the air telling you a secret.

56:29.344 --> 56:32.597
You look up at the sky,
searching for clouds, but all you--

56:50.365 --> 56:51.408
Mr. Whatsit?

56:56.079 --> 56:57.205
Shit!

56:57.288 --> 56:58.581
Officer! Officer!

56:58.665 --> 57:00.208
Whoa, whoa, whoa. Hey, calm down.

57:00.291 --> 57:01.418
-What's going on?
-Shitballs.

57:01.501 --> 57:02.335
Good job, man.

57:02.419 --> 57:04.963
-Lucas! We've been spotted!
-No, no!

57:05.046 --> 57:06.256
Get 'em out of here. Go.

57:06.339 --> 57:08.383
-What about the others?
-Just go! Go, go, go!

57:08.466 --> 57:09.801
Damn it! Okay, come on, guys.

57:14.639 --> 57:18.435
Move! Move! Move! Move!
Move! Move! Move! Move! Move!

57:18.518 --> 57:19.894
Hey, stop right there!

57:19.978 --> 57:22.021
Ashley Klein is a snitch!

57:24.023 --> 57:24.941
Hey!

57:30.405 --> 57:32.574
Open the door! Open the goddamn door!

57:39.831 --> 57:41.458
So you're the reason.

57:42.333 --> 57:45.670
The reason she's been so hard to track.

57:46.504 --> 57:49.883
The thorn in my side.

57:51.176 --> 57:58.183
And after all that effort to hide her,
you bring her here, of all places?

57:59.726 --> 58:00.727
Why?

58:01.895 --> 58:04.898
Why risk her life for the other?

58:06.691 --> 58:08.902
What do you know that I don't?

58:15.909 --> 58:19.120
It's actually holding back,
if you can believe it.

58:19.746 --> 58:21.664
That heat you feel…

58:23.041 --> 58:24.584
weakens it.

58:29.297 --> 58:32.509
But in the cold, it thrives.

58:36.638 --> 58:38.640
I can stop it.

58:39.224 --> 58:41.142
But you're gonna have to start talking.

58:59.911 --> 59:01.079
Go to hell.

59:15.802 --> 59:18.888
In your current state,
I'm afraid that won't work.

59:29.691 --> 59:31.317
Not the sharpest, are we?

59:50.920 --> 59:53.965
You're too late. Cavalry's on its way.

59:54.048 --> 59:55.466
That's all right.

59:56.634 --> 59:57.719
I'll be quick.

1:00:10.481 --> 1:00:11.524
Grocery delivery.

1:00:11.608 --> 1:00:13.026
Where's everyone else?

1:00:13.109 --> 1:00:14.277
Coming.

1:00:17.196 --> 1:00:20.908
Come on, sweetie. Come on down. Come on.

1:00:20.992 --> 1:00:24.120
You get down here right now,
or a monster's gonna eat you.

1:00:26.289 --> 1:00:27.498
Open the door!

1:00:27.582 --> 1:00:28.875
You little shit!

1:00:28.958 --> 1:00:30.251
Get out of the way!

1:00:30.752 --> 1:00:31.961
About goddamn time!

1:00:41.304 --> 1:00:44.390
I got you. That's good. Good, good.

1:00:44.474 --> 1:00:46.851
Hey there.
Where do you think you're going?

1:01:00.406 --> 1:01:01.658
What are you doing?

1:01:02.867 --> 1:01:05.995
Hey, you gotta go. You gotta go. Come on.

1:01:09.707 --> 1:01:11.459
We're gonna get to the woods.

1:01:11.542 --> 1:01:14.003
The kryptonite shit can't get you there.

1:01:14.087 --> 1:01:16.673
Hop, we can't. We can't leave.
We came for Henry.

1:01:16.756 --> 1:01:19.967
Hey. You take this compass.
You're gonna follow it northeast.

1:01:20.051 --> 1:01:23.346
That'll take you to the graveyard.
You're gonna find Nancy and the others.

1:01:23.429 --> 1:01:25.473
Whoa, whoa, whoa. Hey, hey, hey. Hey.

1:01:25.556 --> 1:01:26.474
What is that?

1:01:27.058 --> 1:01:28.434
It's just a failsafe, okay?

1:01:28.518 --> 1:01:30.019
-It's a failsafe.
-No.

1:01:30.103 --> 1:01:31.813
I gotta make sure he goes down with me.

1:01:31.896 --> 1:01:34.524
-No. No, Hop.
-It's the only way. It's the only way.

1:01:34.607 --> 1:01:36.693
I'm not gonna risk losing you.

1:01:36.776 --> 1:01:37.902
I will not risk it.

1:01:38.486 --> 1:01:40.780
-Hopper. No.
-Listen, I want you to know something.

1:01:40.863 --> 1:01:42.365
From here on out,

1:01:42.448 --> 1:01:44.992
I want you to know how proud I am of you.

1:01:45.076 --> 1:01:48.371
I am so proud of you.
I am so proud of what you've overcome.

1:01:50.540 --> 1:01:52.041
I'm proud of who you are.

1:01:52.709 --> 1:01:53.918
No.

1:01:54.001 --> 1:01:57.714
No. No, Hop. Hopper!

1:01:57.797 --> 1:02:01.467
-I love you, Jane.
-Hopper! No! Hopper!

1:02:08.683 --> 1:02:09.642
Hop!

1:02:10.768 --> 1:02:11.978
Hopper!

1:02:14.564 --> 1:02:15.398
Hopper!

1:02:15.982 --> 1:02:16.941
Hop!

1:02:18.025 --> 1:02:19.068
Hopper!

1:02:24.699 --> 1:02:26.242
Hopper!

1:02:26.325 --> 1:02:29.162
Hopper! Hopper!

1:02:30.037 --> 1:02:31.706
Hopper!

1:02:36.878 --> 1:02:38.296
Pulse ox is falling.

1:02:40.840 --> 1:02:41.924
Flatlining!

1:03:04.572 --> 1:03:07.033
All right, kids. Come on.
Find a seat in the back.

1:03:11.412 --> 1:03:12.246
Hi.

1:03:13.331 --> 1:03:14.582
All right.

1:03:14.665 --> 1:03:17.835
Okay, let's have some fun, huh?
This is gonna be great, huh?

1:03:17.919 --> 1:03:19.796
Okay. Let's get our seat belts on, hmm?

1:03:19.879 --> 1:03:22.673
Safety first. Come on. Time's a-wastin'.

1:03:22.757 --> 1:03:23.633
Pretty comfy, huh?

1:03:23.716 --> 1:03:25.092
Not really.

1:03:25.176 --> 1:03:26.886
Oh, sorry.

1:03:26.969 --> 1:03:29.889
Robin, Lucas, do you copy? Over.

1:03:29.972 --> 1:03:30.890
Copy. It's Robin.

1:03:30.973 --> 1:03:32.058
Lucas. I copy.

1:03:33.476 --> 1:03:35.144
We've got a problem here at the MAC.

1:03:35.228 --> 1:03:36.395
What kind of problem?

1:03:36.479 --> 1:03:38.564
Let go of me, you asshole!

1:03:40.191 --> 1:03:42.693
You want to explain to me
what in God's name is going on here?

1:03:42.777 --> 1:03:43.945
Get the hell off me.

1:03:44.028 --> 1:03:46.781
-We've got five missing kids, sir.
-You've lost five kids?

1:03:46.864 --> 1:03:48.199
-How is that possible?
-This woman--

1:03:48.282 --> 1:03:49.367
Joyce Byers.

1:03:49.450 --> 1:03:50.743
She broke into the barracks.

1:03:50.827 --> 1:03:53.496
She's been helping them escape
through some kind of tunnel.

1:03:53.579 --> 1:03:55.414
I'm sorry. Can you repeat that?

1:03:55.498 --> 1:04:00.086
Listen. These kids, they are not safe,
okay? They are in danger.

1:04:00.169 --> 1:04:02.463
And why exactly do you think
they're here, ma'am? Hmm?

1:04:02.547 --> 1:04:03.923
They're under our protection.

1:04:04.006 --> 1:04:06.884
If I may interject, officer.
I've seen what's coming.

1:04:06.968 --> 1:04:11.472
And no disrespect meant,
but you and your men can't protect shit!

1:04:11.556 --> 1:04:13.015
-Private!
-Hey! Hey!

1:04:13.099 --> 1:04:14.517
-Get off him!
-Hey, Private!

1:04:14.600 --> 1:04:18.271
What the hell is wrong with you,
Private? Keep your hands off him.

1:04:23.234 --> 1:04:25.653
Is that all the military does? Hit kids?

1:04:25.736 --> 1:04:28.239
-Will!
-Will! Will! Will!

1:04:28.823 --> 1:04:31.117
Are you okay? Baby, are you okay?

1:04:37.790 --> 1:04:38.916
They're here.

1:05:14.952 --> 1:05:17.121
Take the nearest threat! Engage on sight!

1:05:17.204 --> 1:05:19.081
We're all gonna die! We're all gonna die!

1:05:25.004 --> 1:05:27.173
Guys! Guys! Guys!
Get behind me! Get behind me!

1:05:35.014 --> 1:05:36.432
Get back!

1:05:48.986 --> 1:05:51.572
Under the beds! Under the beds!

1:05:51.656 --> 1:05:56.369
Under the beds! Under the beds!
Under the beds! Under the beds!

1:06:08.089 --> 1:06:09.674
Stay behind me. Stay behind me.

1:06:11.050 --> 1:06:13.594
Move! Move! Move!

1:06:14.887 --> 1:06:15.721
Will!

1:06:26.482 --> 1:06:30.111
We are under attack.
I repeat, we are under attack.

1:06:41.330 --> 1:06:42.915
We gotta go. We gotta go!

1:06:42.999 --> 1:06:44.542
What about the other kids? Shit!

1:06:55.970 --> 1:06:57.388
Go, go, go, go, go!

1:06:59.890 --> 1:07:01.559
Come on, shall we?

1:07:01.642 --> 1:07:02.560
We shall!

1:07:37.094 --> 1:07:39.597
We're getting out of here, all right?
Eyes on me! Stay close!

1:07:39.680 --> 1:07:40.514
Okay, okay.

1:07:40.598 --> 1:07:42.266
Will, come on. Come on!

1:07:47.980 --> 1:07:49.857
-Come on.
-Wait for me, please! Wait!

1:07:49.940 --> 1:07:52.359
I'm not ready to die!

1:07:52.443 --> 1:07:54.862
-Wait up!
-Stay close!

1:07:55.362 --> 1:07:56.989
Derek! Hurry up, let's go!

1:08:00.618 --> 1:08:03.412
-Is everybody okay? Are you guys okay?
-Yeah.

1:08:05.331 --> 1:08:09.210
Okay. The Radio Shack. If we move
quick enough, I think we can make it.

1:08:09.293 --> 1:08:11.087
Get into the tunnels and get out of here.

1:08:11.170 --> 1:08:12.296
-Okay.
-Okay?

1:08:12.379 --> 1:08:14.507
Eyes on me. Remember?

1:08:17.510 --> 1:08:18.969
Stop, stop, stop, stop!

1:08:21.722 --> 1:08:22.598
All right, go!

1:08:26.685 --> 1:08:27.645
Get some!

1:08:30.022 --> 1:08:32.066
Go, go, go! Oh my God.

1:08:39.698 --> 1:08:40.825
Oh my God!

1:08:59.009 --> 1:09:01.303
Just hold on, baby! Hold on!

1:09:12.022 --> 1:09:15.317
-What the hell just happened?
-I have no idea, but I love it!

1:10:57.294 --> 1:10:58.587
Sister.

1:11:00.005 --> 1:11:01.173
Sister.

1:12:07.948 --> 1:12:09.116
Unload!

1:12:18.584 --> 1:12:20.294
Watch out!

1:12:46.862 --> 1:12:47.821
Murray!

1:12:49.865 --> 1:12:51.408
Son of a bitch!

1:12:54.453 --> 1:12:56.372
Oh, shit, shit, shit!

1:13:00.918 --> 1:13:02.503
Whoa!

1:13:05.547 --> 1:13:06.590
The kids!

1:13:06.673 --> 1:13:08.133
Hold on!

1:13:30.447 --> 1:13:32.282
Move, move, move! Let's go, guys!

1:13:37.538 --> 1:13:39.456
Back up, guys! Back up!

1:14:26.211 --> 1:14:30.257
Stay away from him! You stay away!

1:15:12.090 --> 1:15:13.717
Can you see them…

1:15:15.052 --> 1:15:16.094
William?

1:15:18.555 --> 1:15:21.099
Can you see the children?

1:15:21.683 --> 1:15:23.519
Do you know why?

1:15:26.688 --> 1:15:30.776
Why I chose them to reshape the world?

1:15:35.405 --> 1:15:38.408
It's because they are weak.

1:15:42.913 --> 1:15:47.459
Weak in body and mind.

1:15:53.090 --> 1:15:54.091
Please!

1:15:54.675 --> 1:15:56.593
Easily broken.

1:15:57.970 --> 1:16:00.138
Easily reshaped.

1:16:01.557 --> 1:16:03.016
Controlled.

1:16:06.478 --> 1:16:08.313
The perfect vessels.

1:16:10.440 --> 1:16:11.900
And you…

1:16:12.943 --> 1:16:13.986
Will.

1:16:15.112 --> 1:16:16.947
You were the first.

1:16:19.157 --> 1:16:24.871
And you broke so easily.

1:16:30.460 --> 1:16:35.757
You showed me what was possible,

1:16:36.341 --> 1:16:38.135
what I could achieve.

1:16:40.178 --> 1:16:43.140
Some minds, it turns out,

1:16:44.349 --> 1:16:47.060
simply do not belong in this world.

1:16:54.192 --> 1:16:57.029
They belong in mine.

1:17:46.203 --> 1:17:49.164
I was looking for the answers
in somebody else, but…

1:17:49.247 --> 1:17:51.667
I had all the answers.

1:18:04.971 --> 1:18:06.306
Do you wanna be friends?

1:18:11.061 --> 1:18:12.104
I just…

1:18:13.021 --> 1:18:16.983
needed to stop being so goddamn scared.

1:18:24.908 --> 1:18:26.993
Scared of who I really was.

1:18:31.289 --> 1:18:33.583
Wow! It's so good!

1:18:59.025 --> 1:19:00.652
And once I did that,

1:19:01.319 --> 1:19:02.654
I was so free.

1:19:03.530 --> 1:19:05.407
It's like I could fly.
